From: Sama Engine <engine@local>
Subject: [PATCH] renderer_vk: treat VK_SUBOPTIMAL_KHR as success, do not recreate swapchain

Context — the actual bug
------------------------
After every prior hypothesis (vsync, GPU work, swapchain depth, present
mode, per-call timing) the team's first capture with BX_TRACE actually
firing surfaced the real problem in two lines of logcat repeating every
15-17 ms for the entire activity lifetime:

  BGFX vkQueuePresentKHR(...): result = VK_SUBOPTIMAL_KHR
  BGFX Create swapchain numSwapChainImages 5, ...
  BGFX Successfully created swapchain (2251x1080) with 5 images.

bgfx tears down and recreates the swapchain on EVERY frame because
Pixel 9 / Android 16 returns VK_SUBOPTIMAL_KHR from every
vkQueuePresentKHR.  The cost is vkDeviceWaitIdle + vkDestroySwapchainKHR
+ vkCreateSwapchainKHR + image-view recreation per frame, ~15 ms.  That
is what every prior measurement was capturing — backbuffer count,
present mode, GPU work all irrelevant because the swapchain dies
immediately after the frame ships, all that work is thrown away.

Almost certainly Pixel 9's display-cutout situation: activity drawable
region is 2251×1080 (visible in dumpsys SurfaceFlinger as
displayCutoutSafeInsets=Rect(173, 0 - 0, 0)), but the Vulkan surface's
currentExtent reports 2424×1080 (full panel).  Swapchain created at
the smaller activity-region size perpetually SUBOPTIMALs against the
surface's preferred extent.  Rebuilding does NOT clear the flag —
the next present returns SUBOPTIMAL again, and the next, forever.

Why bgfx does this by default
-----------------------------
The Vulkan spec lumps SUBOPTIMAL_KHR with OUT_OF_DATE_KHR as "swapchain
needs attention."  OUT_OF_DATE_KHR is a hard error (the swapchain
genuinely cannot continue to be used and MUST be recreated).
SUBOPTIMAL_KHR is a soft hint ("the surface has a preferred config
your swapchain doesn't match; the present operation completed
successfully but you might want to rebuild eventually").  bgfx's
present-result switch treats both identically — conservative for
correctness, catastrophic for performance on devices like Pixel 9 where
SUBOPTIMAL is permanent.

The fix
-------
Split the cases in both call sites:

  SwapChainVK::acquire    (line ~8225): vkAcquireNextImageKHR result
  SwapChainVK::present    (line ~8307): vkQueuePresentKHR result

VK_ERROR_OUT_OF_DATE_KHR keeps the existing behaviour (set
m_needToRecreateSwapchain, return false on acquire).
VK_SUBOPTIMAL_KHR becomes a separate case: treat as VK_SUCCESS, emit
a one-shot BX_TRACE so the team can confirm it triggered without
flooding logcat (file-static s_samaSuboptimalLogged covers both
sites — one log line per process lifetime).

The frame WAS acquired / presented correctly.  Rendering continues at
the activity-region resolution we asked for (2251×1080), which is the
correct visible area.  We accept "the surface technically allows a
larger swapchain but we chose smaller" forever — that is correct,
intentional, and what the cutout-safe rendering pipeline requires.

Expected impact
---------------
bgfx::frameMs drops from ~16 ms (vsync-pinned by per-frame recreation)
to ~0.1 ms — the original team estimate.  Per-call timing from the
prior patch should now show all four Vulkan calls in sub-ms territory.
FPS reaches panel limit.  No visible artefact: the 2251×1080
activity-region was the correct render target all along; we just stop
discarding our work every frame.

Why this is correct, not just a workaround
------------------------------------------
The Vulkan spec explicitly allows applications to keep using a
swapchain that returns SUBOPTIMAL_KHR (VkSwapchainKHR(3) and the Vulkan
Guide both confirm).  Most production engines (Unreal, Unity, Godot)
ignore SUBOPTIMAL — it is the standard pattern.  bgfx's conservative
"always rebuild" is the outlier and predates platforms where SUBOPTIMAL
became permanent.  Worth proposing upstream alongside the MAILBOX
reorder — either ignore SUBOPTIMAL entirely or expose a flag.

A more invasive "correct" fix would create the swapchain at the
surface's currentExtent (2424×1080) and use viewport+scissor to render
only inside the cutout-safe area.  That avoids the SUBOPTIMAL flag at
the source but requires platform-side knowledge of cutout insets being
plumbed into the renderer, and pays the cost of allocating swapchain
images we never use.  Worth doing eventually for cutout-aware
rendering (status bar reveal, edge-to-edge fullscreen), but blocks on
plumbing we don't yet have.  Treating SUBOPTIMAL as success is the
right fix today; the cutout-aware swapchain is the right fix for the
future and they don't conflict.

Counterpart commit on engine side documents the diagnostic and the
decision; see docs/NOTES.md "Follow-up (2026-06-18, root cause found
— SUBOPTIMAL_KHR swapchain rebuild loop)".
---
 bgfx/src/renderer_vk.cpp | 38 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++----
 1 file changed, 34 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

diff --git a/bgfx/src/renderer_vk.cpp b/bgfx/src/renderer_vk.cpp
--- a/bgfx/src/renderer_vk.cpp
+++ b/bgfx/src/renderer_vk.cpp
@@ -156,6 +156,13 @@
 		{ VK_PRESENT_MODE_IMMEDIATE_KHR,    false, "VK_PRESENT_MODE_IMMEDIATE_KHR"    },
 	};

+	// Sama suboptimal-as-success diagnostic — see
+	// patches/bgfx_android_vk_suboptimal_no_recreate.patch.
+	// One-shot trace gate so logcat doesn't flood when the surface
+	// reports SUBOPTIMAL every frame (Pixel 9 / Android 16 display
+	// cutout behaviour).
+	static bool s_samaSuboptimalLogged = false;
+
 #define VK_IMPORT_FUNC(_optional, _func) PFN_##_func _func
 #define VK_IMPORT_INSTANCE_FUNC VK_IMPORT_FUNC
 #define VK_IMPORT_DEVICE_FUNC   VK_IMPORT_FUNC
@@ -8216,10 +8223,23 @@
 				return false;

 			case VK_ERROR_OUT_OF_DATE_KHR:
-			case VK_SUBOPTIMAL_KHR:
 				m_needToRecreateSwapchain = true;
 				return false;

+			case VK_SUBOPTIMAL_KHR:
+				// SUBOPTIMAL is a hint, not an error — the frame WAS
+				// acquired; the surface just has a preferred config
+				// the swapchain doesn't match.  On Pixel 9 / Android 16
+				// the display cutout makes this permanent: rebuilding
+				// the swapchain doesn't fix it, just thrashes.
+				// Treat as success; log once.
+				if (!s_samaSuboptimalLogged)
+				{
+					BX_TRACE("Sama: vkAcquireNextImageKHR returned VK_SUBOPTIMAL_KHR — treating as success (will not recreate swapchain)");
+					s_samaSuboptimalLogged = true;
+				}
+				break;
+
 			default:
 				BX_ASSERT(VK_SUCCESS == result, "vkAcquireNextImageKHR(...); VK error 0x%x: %s", result, getName(result) );
 				return false;
@@ -8282,10 +8302,25 @@
 				break;

 			case VK_ERROR_OUT_OF_DATE_KHR:
-			case VK_SUBOPTIMAL_KHR:
 				m_needToRecreateSwapchain = true;
 				break;

+			case VK_SUBOPTIMAL_KHR:
+				// SUBOPTIMAL means the frame WAS presented; the
+				// surface just reports a preferred config that
+				// doesn't match the swapchain.  Pixel 9 / Android 16
+				// reports this every frame due to display-cutout
+				// inset mismatch — rebuilding the swapchain costs
+				// vkDeviceWaitIdle + destroy + create + image views
+				// every frame and does NOT clear the SUBOPTIMAL flag.
+				// Treat as success; log once.
+				if (!s_samaSuboptimalLogged)
+				{
+					BX_TRACE("Sama: vkQueuePresentKHR returned VK_SUBOPTIMAL_KHR — treating as success (will not recreate swapchain)");
+					s_samaSuboptimalLogged = true;
+				}
+				break;
+
 			default:
 				BX_ASSERT(VK_SUCCESS == result, "vkQueuePresentKHR(...); VK error 0x%x: %s", result, getName(result) );
 				break;
